    <fn id="t002fn001" class="fn" xmlns="">
     <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <span class="sup">m</span> denotes ‘mechanistic’ traits, whose relevance has been identified directly from physiological studies, and
     </p>
    </fn>
    <fn id="t002fn002" class="fn" xmlns="">
     <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <span class="sup">f</span> ‘functional’ traits relating to size or to the ‘leaf economics spectrum’. Traits that span both groupings are designated as 
      <span class="sup">f,m</span>.
     </p>
    </fn>
